Hudson Street, west side, north from Abingdon Square just below Bethune Street, and showing two houses on the N.E. corner of 12th Street, across the park, which are shortly to be demolished. The Laura Spellman Y.W.C.A., on the S.W. corner of 12th Street, is flying its flag at half-mast. Other pictures of these buildings are also filed under Abingdon Square.

May 30, 1929.

P. L. Sperr, Photographer.

General Electric Supply Corporation, 591, 587-585 Hudson Street, west side, from Bethune to Bank Streets. At this point the distance between Hudson and Greenwich Streets is at its minimum. See also Abingdon Square.
March 12, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.

Hudson Street, west side, from Bethune to Jane Streets, seen across Abingdon Square (q.v.).
March 12, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.

597 to 607-609 Hudson Street, west side, Abingdon Square, from Bethune to 12th (formerly Troy) Streets. No. 599 Hudson Street (16 Abingdon Square) is the home (since 1929) of the Jeffersonians, the Tammany club for the Third Assembly District South. See Abingdon Square. The clearing in the foreground is the site of the Abingdon Hotel at 7 Abingdon Square. No. 607-609 is the Laura Spellman Y. W. C. A. March 12, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.
